article.headline: Tulane 79, St. John's 71
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Kevin Sims and Matt Wheaton scored 21 points each to lead Tulane to a fifth place finish in the Rainbow Classic with a 79-71 win over St. John's on Saturday. Matt Wheaton added 12 for the Green Wave (8-4). Anthony Mason Jr. led the Red Storm (5-4) with 18 points and Sean Evans added 11. Down by six midway through the second half, Tulane went on a 20-4 run to take control of the game, 66-56, with 2:22 remaining. St. John's went nearly eight minutes without a field goal during the stretch. Tulane made 13-of-16 free throws in the final two minutes to seal the victory. The Green Wave shot 27-of-34 from the line for the game, including 11-of-15 for Sims. St. John's led 38-32 at the half.
